    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SRS Indication TLV Padding Byte Comparison\n\n### Summary\nThe `eq_srs_indication_PDU` function in the nFAPI utilities was incorrectly comparing SRS report TLVs by including padding bytes in the comparison. This caused false negatives when two TLVs contained identical valid data but had different values in their padding bytes, leading to failed equality checks during message processing.\n\nThe issue occurred because the original implementation used a simple loop comparing all 32-bit words without considering that the last word might contain a mix of valid data bytes and padding bytes that should be ignored according to the SCF specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: \n  * Modified `eq_srs_indication_report_tlv` to properly handle padding bytes by calculating complete words vs partial words and using bitmasks to compare only valid bytes\n  * Updated `copy_srs_indication_report_tlv` for consistency to preserve padding bytes during copy operations\n  * Added detailed comments explaining the padding byte handling logic\n\nWhen processing SRS indications with report TLVs where the length is not a multiple of 4 bytes, the function now correctly ignores the padding bytes during comparison. For example, a TLV with length=5 will only compare the first 5 bytes of data rather than all 8 bytes in the underlying 32-bit word array.\n\nThis resolves intermittent failures in SRS indication message validation where identical reports were incorrectly flagged as different due to uninitialized padding byte values.\n"
}